This paper is primarily focused on object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques to achieve effective computation and accuracy trade-off, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes a method for reducing FLOPs in computational intensive layers, which involves optimizing the neural network architecture, and this could be considered a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of resource constraint devices, which could be categorized under neural engineering (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of various object detection models, which could be considered a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM).
